Q44A1:
I have Follicular Lymphoma. At the present time there is no cure for it.
In follicular lymphoma, there is a transposing of the 14th or 18th chromosone in the DNA. When I asked my onocologist about why that happens, he told me that they do not have an answer for that. My daughter is soon to have her Doctorate in Plant Genetics and when I asked her about it she told me that the reason they have been unable to find out is because there are numerous factors that have to come together in order for the cancer cell to survive. So far they have not been able to determine what factors those are. 
In the meantime, I am left with questions for which there are no answers. I would like to find answers!
